3
00:01:51,220 --> 00:01:52,880
Baroque Works?!

4
00:01:53,340 --> 00:01:54,890
Never heard of 'em!

5
00:01:54,890 --> 00:01:57,470
Any proof a company
like that even exists?

6
00:01:57,470 --> 00:02:00,890
We're ordinary citizens
of Alabasta, Mr. Marine.

7
00:02:01,390 --> 00:02:04,100
Are you trying to harm
honest people in this chaos?

8
00:02:07,980 --> 00:02:08,980
Sergeant Major!

9
00:02:09,570 --> 00:02:11,400
Why are you hesitating?!

10
00:02:12,740 --> 00:02:15,870
If we wait for proof, we'll be too late!

11
00:02:15,870 --> 00:02:17,580
It's up to you to spot the enemy!

12
00:02:18,030 --> 00:02:20,160
Yes, ma'am! Our apologies!

13
00:02:20,750 --> 00:02:22,460
Almost 4:30...

14
00:02:22,460 --> 00:02:23,920
We're running out of time...

15
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:27,750
The clock...!

16
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:30,630
Ribbit, ribbit, ribbit, ribbit...

17
00:02:30,630 --> 00:02:32,760
Hey, listen, Mr. 7.

18
00:02:32,760 --> 00:02:35,890
I think this is quite
an important mission.

19
00:02:35,890 --> 00:02:39,350
That's right, Miss Father's Day.

20
00:02:39,350 --> 00:02:44,560
I think we might be getting
a huge promotion! Ribbit, ribbit.

21
00:02:46,810 --> 00:02:48,900
I hope that's the plan.

22
00:02:48,900 --> 00:02:52,610
I hope so. I hope so,
Miss Father's Day.

23
00:02:52,610 --> 00:02:56,160
After all, our plan is to shoot
a cannonball into the crowd

24
00:02:56,160 --> 00:03:01,160
using this gargaaantuan cannon!

25
00:03:01,160 --> 00:03:01,990
So I hope so!

26
00:03:06,460 --> 00:03:09,420
Ribbit! It's almost time, Mr. 7!

27
00:03:10,170 --> 00:03:13,210
Primed and ready!

28
00:03:27,850 --> 00:03:28,980
Tell me, runt...

29
00:03:29,730 --> 00:03:33,740
What exactly do I "not get"?

30
00:03:42,540 --> 00:03:44,410
Gum-Gum...

31
00:03:44,830 --> 00:03:46,620
Gatling!

32
00:03:54,760 --> 00:03:56,420
Don't you understand?

33
00:03:56,420 --> 00:04:02,560
Any second now, you'll keel over
from the venom in that wound.

34
00:04:04,640 --> 00:04:07,730
Your body has to be
going numb by now.

35
00:04:09,190 --> 00:04:12,360
Regardless of this duel's outcome,

36
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:15,650
you'll wind up buried
under this temple.

37
00:04:15,650 --> 00:04:18,200
Fifteen seconds until the attack!

38
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:23,280
The target is the center of the square!

39
00:04:23,280 --> 00:04:24,330
Ribbit, ribbit.

40
00:04:24,330 --> 00:04:26,120
Ignite!

41
00:04:27,580 --> 00:04:30,460
Hey, Nami! What the hell
are you trying to do?!

42
00:04:30,960 --> 00:04:32,710
We don't have time for this!

43
00:04:32,710 --> 00:04:35,170
If we fail, we die!

44
00:04:35,170 --> 00:04:36,170
Hey!

45
00:04:36,170 --> 00:04:40,800
I know that, so be quiet!
I'm doing some calculations!

46
00:04:41,300 --> 00:04:44,060
Be quiet?! At least explain
why we're stacked up!

47
00:04:44,060 --> 00:04:46,640
What the hell are you gonna do?!

48
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:48,180
You're about to find out!

49
00:04:48,680 --> 00:04:49,940
Ready?!

50
00:04:49,940 --> 00:04:51,810
Ribbit, ribbit, ribbit, ribbit...

51
00:04:51,810 --> 00:04:54,520
Hey, listen, Mr. 7!

52
00:04:54,520 --> 00:04:57,040
This is a rare occasion! 
I wanna do a countdown!

53
00:04:57,570 --> 00:05:01,570
Is that your plan? That's good!
That's good! Sounds interesting!

54
00:05:02,620 --> 00:05:05,120
The forecast calls for a typhoon!

55
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:08,580
– Thirteen seconds until the attack!
– Thirteen seconds until the attack!

56
00:05:10,250 --> 00:05:13,210
Cyclone Tempo!

57
00:05:13,210 --> 00:05:18,760
H-Hey! Cyclone Tempo is just
a boomerang trick for after-parties!

58
00:05:19,130 --> 00:05:20,720
Up the clock tower you go!

59
00:05:35,310 --> 00:05:37,440
What the heck...? They're coming up!

60
00:05:38,070 --> 00:05:41,400
Chopper! Jump to where Sanji is!

61
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:42,360
– What?!
– What?!

62
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:43,660
Don't tell me...

63
00:05:43,660 --> 00:05:47,330
Is she saying the plan is to jump
all the way up like this?!

64
00:05:47,330 --> 00:05:49,890
Sanji, you get what
I'm going for, right?

65
00:05:49,890 --> 00:05:51,250
We don't have time!

66
00:05:51,250 --> 00:05:53,330
I think I get the gist of it, but...

67
00:05:53,330 --> 00:05:55,880
Ah, whatever! I just have to go for it!

68
00:05:56,290 --> 00:05:58,250
Sounds like we don't
have time to think!

69
00:05:58,250 --> 00:05:59,670
I'm counting on you, Tony!

70
00:05:59,670 --> 00:06:02,340
Okay! Hang on tight, Vivi!

71
00:06:04,090 --> 00:06:06,100
I see... That's what we're doing.

72
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:08,470
Chopper! Get on my right leg!

73
00:06:08,470 --> 00:06:09,890
Got it!

74
00:06:10,390 --> 00:06:11,600
– Eleven!
– Eleven!

75
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:15,650
There! Heads up, Zoro!

76
00:06:15,650 --> 00:06:17,150
Alright! Nice work!

77
00:06:19,730 --> 00:06:21,860
So I just have to get
them up there, right?!

78
00:06:21,860 --> 00:06:23,490
– Ten!
– Ten!

79
00:06:23,490 --> 00:06:24,910
Zoro!

80
00:06:25,280 --> 00:06:26,780
Right! Leave it to me!

81
00:06:27,370 --> 00:06:28,330
With your swords?!

82
00:06:28,330 --> 00:06:30,790
Don't be scared, dummy!
It's the back of the blade!

83
00:06:30,790 --> 00:06:31,870
Get a good foothold!

84
00:06:31,870 --> 00:06:32,870
Oh, okay!

85
00:06:32,870 --> 00:06:34,170
– Nine!
– Nine!

86
00:06:34,170 --> 00:06:36,540
Careful, Vivi! We've got
some weirdos up there!

87
00:06:36,540 --> 00:06:38,130
Yes, we're well acquainted!

88
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:40,420
No!

89
00:06:41,880 --> 00:06:43,510
Miss Wednesday!

90
00:06:43,510 --> 00:06:48,390
Ribbit, ribbit, ribbit! She's the agent
who betrayed the company!

91
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:50,560
Crap, they've noticed!

92
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:51,350
What?!

93
00:06:51,850 --> 00:06:54,390
Wait a sec! We're in the air!

94
00:06:54,390 --> 00:06:56,350
If they shoot at us...!

95
00:06:57,610 --> 00:07:00,730
I'm positive there's nothing
of value to you in this country!

96
00:07:01,320 --> 00:07:02,740
Isn't that right?!

97
00:07:02,740 --> 00:07:04,820
What's the point in giving your life...

98
00:07:05,450 --> 00:07:07,280
for someone else's ambition?!

99
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:12,660
Just ditch a friend or two.
It'll save you some trouble!

100
00:07:13,290 --> 00:07:16,540
You're all complete simpletons.

101
00:07:18,540 --> 00:07:22,510
That's why I said...
you just don't get it...!

102
00:07:22,880 --> 00:07:24,010
Vivi...

103
00:07:27,260 --> 00:07:30,140
She tells people
not to risk their lives...

104
00:07:30,140 --> 00:07:33,720
but she's the first to lay down
her own to save others.

105
00:07:34,270 --> 00:07:36,480
If we don't help her, she'll die.

106
00:07:36,480 --> 00:07:37,730
You guys will kill her.

107
00:07:37,730 --> 00:07:39,900
Get it through your thick head!

108
00:07:40,230 --> 00:07:44,320
I'm saying to just cast aside
that burdensome girl–

109
00:07:45,110 --> 00:07:47,700
I don't want her to die!

110
00:07:47,700 --> 00:07:49,870
'Cause she's my friend!

111
00:07:50,450 --> 00:07:53,620
As long as she refuses
to give up on her country...

112
00:07:54,250 --> 00:07:57,580
we'll be right there fighting beside her!

113
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:00,920
Even if you all die in the process?

114
00:08:01,420 --> 00:08:04,170
If we die, we die.

115
00:08:04,880 --> 00:08:07,260
Adjust! Ribbit-Ribbit Gun!

116
00:08:07,260 --> 00:08:08,840
This is an unexpected catch!

117
00:08:09,220 --> 00:08:11,680
Adjust! Yellow Gun!

118
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:15,640
This is good! This is good!
They're sitting ducks!

119
00:08:15,640 --> 00:08:19,650
You bastards! How dare you
point guns at Vivi?!

120
00:08:19,650 --> 00:08:22,020
This is bad! Those two are snipers!

121
00:08:22,020 --> 00:08:22,820
Chopper!

122
00:08:22,820 --> 00:08:24,440
I'll go ahead and send you up!

123
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:27,070
I'll change the direction,
but then it's up to you!

124
00:08:27,070 --> 00:08:28,490
Huh?! Me?!

125
00:08:28,490 --> 00:08:30,070
Seven seconds left!

126
00:08:30,070 --> 00:08:32,450
Do something!

127
00:08:34,740 --> 00:08:37,710
All set? I'm gonna send
you up, Chopper! Vivi!

128
00:08:37,710 --> 00:08:38,910
Okay!

129
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,130
Ready...!

130
00:08:41,130 --> 00:08:41,790
Smash!

131
00:08:43,040 --> 00:08:44,170
Go!

132
00:08:44,170 --> 00:08:45,550
Hey, listen.

133
00:08:45,550 --> 00:08:47,260
Our bullets are designed...

134
00:08:48,050 --> 00:08:50,720
...to collide and explode!

135
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:55,430
Zoro!

136
00:08:59,770 --> 00:09:00,850
That numbskull!

137
00:09:01,230 --> 00:09:02,520
He took a direct hit...!

138
00:09:03,230 --> 00:09:04,690
Ready, Vivi?!

139
00:09:04,690 --> 00:09:07,400
With all your might, please, Tony!

140
00:09:10,950 --> 00:09:12,740
Ribbit, ribbit. It's no use...

141
00:09:12,740 --> 00:09:13,820
...dodging!

142
00:09:13,820 --> 00:09:15,120
– Smash!
– Smash!

143
00:09:16,040 --> 00:09:16,790
– Who the...?!
– Who the...?!

144
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,080
– What the...?!
– What the...?!

145
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:27,590
Where's Miss Wednesday?!

146
00:09:27,590 --> 00:09:29,590
What happened?!

147
00:09:31,590 --> 00:09:35,010
Peacock String...

148
00:09:35,510 --> 00:09:36,720
She's up there!

149
00:09:39,390 --> 00:09:44,190
– Go!
– Go!

150
00:09:49,110 --> 00:09:54,240
Despite all your bluster,
it's getting harder to move, isn't it?

151
00:09:55,740 --> 00:09:58,200
You look pathetic, Straw Hat.

152
00:10:02,160 --> 00:10:03,330
...Slasher!

153
00:10:08,590 --> 00:10:10,340
Ribbit, ribbit! Sorry!

154
00:10:10,880 --> 00:10:11,630
You missed!

155
00:10:17,430 --> 00:10:19,310
Runback!

156
00:10:22,940 --> 00:10:24,190
Alright!

157
00:10:47,330 --> 00:10:49,670
– Vivi!
– Vivi!

158
00:10:49,670 --> 00:10:51,880
Hey, you brats!

159
00:10:52,260 --> 00:10:54,510
You used the shortcut
again, didn't you?!

160
00:10:54,510 --> 00:10:56,340
It's the gatekeeper! Run!

161
00:10:57,010 --> 00:11:01,350
Lieutenants, please talk
some sense into those hooligans!

162
00:11:02,810 --> 00:11:03,600
Sure.

163
00:11:04,810 --> 00:11:07,060
Heading out, Princess Vivi?

164
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:09,190
Yep! To our secret base!

165
00:11:09,190 --> 00:11:11,230
Very well. Have fun.

166
00:11:13,900 --> 00:11:15,360
Where did Princess Vivi go?

167
00:11:17,030 --> 00:11:18,280
I can't tell you.

168
00:11:18,280 --> 00:11:19,410
It's a secret.

169
00:11:22,290 --> 00:11:23,450
The clock tower, huh?

170
00:11:54,690 --> 00:11:56,240
Did she stop it...?

171
00:12:22,220 --> 00:12:24,180
What do you know...? You survived.

172
00:12:25,060 --> 00:12:27,640
Wh... What happened to the attack?

173
00:12:29,100 --> 00:12:30,690
What fell on me?

174
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:32,610
Ouch!

175
00:12:36,610 --> 00:12:38,110
Is something wrong?

176
00:12:38,110 --> 00:12:40,110
Seems like we hit a snag.

177
00:12:40,110 --> 00:12:42,070
What is Vivi doing?

178
00:12:45,080 --> 00:12:46,660
Guys, we've got a problem!

179
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:48,160
Vivi!

180
00:12:48,540 --> 00:12:52,080
The cannonball has a timer!
If we don't do something, it'll explode!

181
00:12:53,340 --> 00:12:56,510
What?!

182
00:12:58,340 --> 00:13:01,300
You despicable wretch!

183
00:13:03,430 --> 00:13:09,180
At the very least, Mr. Cobra,
give me some credit for being thorough.

184
00:13:09,180 --> 00:13:13,690
All plans must account
for unforeseen circumstances.

185
00:13:15,520 --> 00:13:18,780
Even if the cannoneer is incapacitated,

186
00:13:18,780 --> 00:13:21,780
the cannonball will
detonate on its own.

187
00:13:21,780 --> 00:13:25,490
It's simply delayed
by a few dozen seconds.

188
00:13:26,370 --> 00:13:30,160
I had hoped it would be fired
into the center of the square...

189
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:35,170
but the damage will be
catastrophic, regardless.

190
00:13:41,550 --> 00:13:44,390
If we do this, the rebellion will stop.

191
00:13:45,220 --> 00:13:48,350
If we do that, the rebellion will stop.

192
00:13:49,680 --> 00:13:54,310
I can't stand your wide-eyed idealism.

193
00:13:58,730 --> 00:14:00,610
Let me tell you something.

194
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:09,410
You can't save this country.

195
00:14:12,620 --> 00:14:14,750
Dammit! What the hell...?!

196
00:14:14,750 --> 00:14:17,000
We stopped the attack,
but the cannonball...

197
00:14:17,590 --> 00:14:19,130
...has a timer?!

198
00:14:19,760 --> 00:14:23,010
If it can level a five-kilometer area,

199
00:14:23,010 --> 00:14:25,590
the square and the city are done for!

200
00:14:27,810 --> 00:14:30,600
What do we do now?!

201
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:35,100
You're telling me we never even
had a shot at stopping the explosion?!

202
00:14:37,650 --> 00:14:40,230
He made us come
this far to look for it...!

203
00:14:40,780 --> 00:14:43,450
He even announced the attack...!

204
00:14:43,450 --> 00:14:44,860
Just how far...

205
00:14:49,450 --> 00:14:53,750
does he have to go
to make fools of us?!

206
00:14:55,290 --> 00:14:59,630
Just how much does
he have to mock us...?!

207
00:15:02,300 --> 00:15:05,550
Crocodile!

208
00:15:15,770 --> 00:15:17,150
As long as she refuses...

209
00:15:17,560 --> 00:15:19,520
to give up on her country...

210
00:15:20,610 --> 00:15:23,570
we'll be right there fighting beside her!

211
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,510
You...

212
00:15:43,510 --> 00:15:44,800
can't...

213
00:15:48,890 --> 00:15:50,600
beat me!

214
00:15:52,390 --> 00:15:55,930
You finally manage to speak
and that's all you have to say?

215
00:15:58,190 --> 00:16:04,570
What fitting final words...
for a loser about to kick the bucket.

216
00:16:04,570 --> 00:16:06,110
You're nothing but talk!

217
00:16:09,870 --> 00:16:13,450
I'm the man who's gonna be
King of the Pirates!

218
00:16:13,950 --> 00:16:15,700
Listen up, brat.

219
00:16:15,700 --> 00:16:18,460
If you knew anything about this sea,

220
00:16:18,460 --> 00:16:22,420
you'd think twice before
spouting such drivel.

221
00:16:24,300 --> 00:16:25,920
I thought I told you...

222
00:16:26,550 --> 00:16:31,140
rookies like you are
a dime a dozen on this sea.

223
00:16:34,620 --> 00:16:37,600
But as you experience its magnitude...

224
00:16:38,520 --> 00:16:41,810
you'll abandon those kinds of dreams!

225
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,080
I'm the man...

226
00:16:59,670 --> 00:17:02,170
who will surpass you!

227
00:17:04,340 --> 00:17:05,840
Was that...?

228
00:17:05,840 --> 00:17:07,510
That bird guy...

229
00:17:12,640 --> 00:17:13,430
Pell!

230
00:17:14,970 --> 00:17:17,180
This place sure
brings back memories...

231
00:17:17,180 --> 00:17:19,810
The Sand Sand Clan's secret base...

232
00:17:19,810 --> 00:17:21,190
Pell, listen!

233
00:17:21,190 --> 00:17:25,230
The cannonball has a timing device!
It's going to explode at any moment!

234
00:17:21,190 --> 00:17:27,900
Back then, you always seemed
to find new ways to cause us trouble.

235
00:17:29,110 --> 00:17:31,910
Why is Princess Vivi in
the ammunition storehouse?!

236
00:17:34,160 --> 00:17:35,660
Hey, what happened?!

237
00:17:35,660 --> 00:17:37,330
I heard a boom!

238
00:17:40,040 --> 00:17:44,840
We've told you time and again to stay
away from the ammunition storehouse!

239
00:17:45,670 --> 00:17:46,550
Pell!

240
00:17:46,920 --> 00:17:48,210
Lieutenant Pell!

241
00:17:49,460 --> 00:17:52,970
I was trying to make fireworks, 
but it was a bust!

242
00:17:52,970 --> 00:17:56,220
You see, it's the anniversary of
the day that you joined the army–

243
00:17:58,060 --> 00:17:59,600
What are you doing?!

244
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:02,020
How many times have I told you...

245
00:18:02,020 --> 00:18:03,900
to never come near this place!

246
00:18:06,020 --> 00:18:09,400
You! Do you know
what you just did?!

247
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:11,530
I'll have you expelled
from the palace! You–

248
00:18:11,530 --> 00:18:12,570
Wait, Igaram!

249
00:18:13,950 --> 00:18:15,280
Let them be...

250
00:18:18,660 --> 00:18:20,410
What if it wasn't simply...

251
00:18:22,580 --> 00:18:23,920
a few scratches?

252
00:18:30,550 --> 00:18:31,800
Keep going!

253
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:33,180
Higher!

254
00:18:33,180 --> 00:18:34,890
I said higher!

255
00:18:35,640 --> 00:18:39,810
Princess Vivi, promise not
to tell your father, okay?!

256
00:18:42,810 --> 00:18:48,070
He expressly forbade me
from taking you flying!

257
00:18:48,070 --> 00:18:49,320
Then just drop me off!

258
00:18:49,320 --> 00:18:51,650
I'll never forgive you
for earlier, meanie!

259
00:18:53,650 --> 00:18:57,410
You're the one who said you'd
do anything to make it up to me!

260
00:19:03,620 --> 00:19:04,870
Hey, Pell.

261
00:19:04,870 --> 00:19:05,670
Yes?

262
00:19:05,670 --> 00:19:08,250
Why are you always training so hard?

263
00:19:08,250 --> 00:19:09,630
Because I'm a guard.

264
